    "Python integer division, like integer division in C and some other languages, truncates the remainder and returns an integer. At least it does in version 2. In version 3, Python returns a floating point number. You can get a sneak preview of this feature in Python 2 by importing the module from the future features:\n",
    "\n",
    "    from __future__ import division"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Alternatively, you can convert one of the integers to a floating point number, in which case the division function returns another floating point number."
