    "## Lists\n",
    "So far, we have numbers and strings. We also need a way to keep a group of similar items together. Python does this using a data type called a **list**.\n",
    "\n",
    "A list in Python is just like a shopping list or a list of numbers. The list of elements has a defined order and you can add to it or remove from it.\n",
    "\n",
    "Here are some simple lists:"
   ]
  },
  {
