  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We see a few other boolean operators here, all of which which should be self-explanatory. Less than, equality, non-equality, and so on.\n",
    "\n",
    "Particularly interesting is the 1 == 1.0 test, which is true, since even though the two objects are different data types (integer and floating point number), they have the same *value*. \n",
    "\n",
    "There is another boolean operator **is**, that tests whether two objects are the same object:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 81,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
